    "doi": null,
    "title_en": "First measurement of $\\mathbf{\\rm Ξ_{\\rm c}^{0}}$ production in $\\mathbf{Pb}-\\mathbf{Pb}$ collisions at $\\mathbf{\\sqrt{\\textit{s}_{\\rm NN}}}$ = 5.02 TeV",
    "abstract_en": "The ALICE Collaboration reports the first measurement of the production of prompt $Ξ_{\\mathrm c}^{0}$ baryons in nucleus$-$nucleus collisions by analyzing data from $\\mathrm{Pb}-\\mathrm{Pb}$ collisions at $\\sqrt{s_{\\mathrm{NN}}}~=5.02~\\mathrm{TeV}$. The production and transverse-momentum ($p_{\\mathrm T}$) differential spectra of $Ξ_{\\mathrm c}^{0}$ are particularly sensitive to the hadronization process and to strangeness production in the quark--gluon plasma formed in high-energy heavy-ion collisions. The $Ξ_{\\mathrm c}^{0}$ baryons are reconstructed at midrapidity ($|y|<0.5$) in the transverse-momentum intervals $3<p_{\\mathrm T}~<12~\\mathrm{GeV}/c$ and $4<p_{\\mathrm T}~<12~\\mathrm{GeV}/c$ in the 0$-$10% and 30$-$50% centrality intervals, respectively. The nuclear modification factor ($R_{\\mathrm{AA}}$) reaches values up to 3 in the interval $3<p_{\\mathrm T}~<4~\\mathrm{GeV}/c$, which is the largest value measured so far for charm hadrons. Model predictions are compatible with the measured $R_{\\mathrm{AA}}$, while, in the measured $p_{\\mathrm T}$ intervals, they underestimate the production yield as well as the measured $Ξ_{\\mathrm c}^{0}/\\mathrm{D}^{0}$, $Ξ_{\\mathrm c}^{0}/Λ_{\\mathrm c}^{+}$, and $Ξ_{\\mathrm c}^{0}/\\mathrm{D}^{+}_{\\mathrm s}$ yield ratios.",
